t=warm", which re-instates the old behaviour. I got several mails<br />telling me that cold reboots works on some hardware that didn't use to reboot<br />cleanly before. As the cold reboot is the safer thing to do anyway (anything<br />which successfully warm-boots should cold-boot no problem) it's now the<br />default (it will be the default in 2.0.22+ too), and you can override it it<br />you want to. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
